WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.787
{"en":"--- lesson 28  Five pounds too dear ","ch":"五磅也太贵 "}

2
00:00:04.937 --> 00:00:11.239
{"en":"Small boats loaded with wares sped to the great liner as she was entering the harbour. ^ ","ch":"当一艘大型班船进港的时候， 许多小船载着各种杂货快速向客轮驶来。  "}

3
00:00:11.389 --> 00:00:16.281
{"en":"Before she had anchored,  the men from the boats had climbed on board^ ","ch":"大船还未下锚。 小船上的人就纷纷爬上客轮。  "}

4
00:00:16.431 --> 00:00:27.514
{"en":"and the decks were soon covered with colourful rugs from Persia,  silks from India,  copper coffee pots,  and beautiful handmade silverware. ^ ","ch":"一会儿工夫， 甲板上就摆满了色彩斑斓的波斯地毯。 印度丝绸。 铜咖啡壶以及手工制作的漂亮的银器。  "}

5
00:00:27.664 --> 00:00:30.361
{"en":"It was difficult not to be tempted. ^ ","ch":"要想不为这些东西所动心是很困难的。  "}

6
00:00:30.511 --> 00:00:35.115
{"en":"Many of the tourists on board had begun bargaining with the tradesmen, ^ ","ch":"船上的许多游客开始同商贩讨价还价起来，  "}

7
00:00:35.265 --> 00:00:40.105
{"en":"but I decide not to buy anything until I had disembarked. ^ ","ch":"但我打定主意上岸之前什么也不买。  "}

8
00:00:40.255 --> 00:00:47.994
{"en":"I had no sooner got off the ship than I was assailed by a man who wanted to sell me a diamond ring. ^ ","ch":"我刚下船， 就被一个人截住， 他向我兜售一枚钻石戒指。  "}

9
00:00:48.144 --> 00:00:56.901
{"en":"I had no intention of buying one,  but I could not conceal the fact that I was impressed by the size of the diamonds. ^ ","ch":"我根本不想买， 但我不能掩饰这样一个事实：其钻石之大给我留下了深刻的印象。  "}

10
00:00:57.051 --> 00:01:00.036
{"en":"Some of them were as big as marbles. ^ ","ch":"有的钻石像玻璃球那么大。  "}

11
00:01:00.186 --> 00:01:05.156
{"en":"The man went to great lengths to prove that the diamonds were real. ^ ","ch":"那人竭力想证明那钻石是真货。  "}

12
00:01:05.306 --> 00:01:13.881
{"en":"As we were walking past a shop,  he held a diamond firmly against the window and made a deep impression in the glass. ^ ","ch":"我们路过一家商店时， 他将一颗钻石使劲地往橱窗上一按， 在玻璃上留下一道深痕。  "}

13
00:01:14.031 --> 00:01:17.460
{"en":"It took me over half an hour to get rid of him. ^ ","ch":"我花了半个多小时才摆脱了他的纠缠。  "}

14
00:01:17.610 --> 00:01:22.554
{"en":"The next man to approach me was selling expensive pens and watches. ^ ","ch":"向我兜售的第二个人是卖名贵钢笔和手表的。  "}

15
00:01:22.704 --> 00:01:25.636
{"en":"I examined one of the pens closely. ^ ","ch":"我仔细察看了一枝钢笔，  "}

16
00:01:25.786 --> 00:01:28.222
{"en":"It certainly looked genuine. ^ ","ch":"那看上去确实不假，  "}

17
00:01:28.372 --> 00:01:36.555
{"en":"At the base of the gold cap,  the words 'made in the U. S. A' had been neatly inscribed. ^ ","ch":"金笔帽下方整齐地刻有“美国制造”字样。  "}

18
00:01:36.705 --> 00:01:46.038
{"en":"The man said that the pen was worth $50,  but as a special favour,  he would let me have it for $30. ^ ","ch":"那人说那支笔值50英镑， 作为特别优惠， 他愿意让我出30英镑成交。  "}

19
00:01:46.188 --> 00:01:53.744
{"en":"I shook my head and held up five fingers indicating that I was willing to pay $5. ^ ","ch":"我摇摇头， 伸出5根手指表示我只愿出5镑钱。  "}

20
00:01:53.894 --> 00:02:05.708
{"en":"Gesticulating wildly,  the man acted as if he found my offer outrageous,  but he eventually reduced the price to $10. ^ ","ch":"那人激动地打着手势， 仿佛我的出价使他不能容忍。 但他终于把价钱降到了10英镑。  "}

21
00:02:05.858 --> 00:02:15.870
{"en":"Shrugging my shoulders,  I began to walk away when,  a moment later,  he ran after me and thrust the pen into my hands. ^ ","ch":"我耸耸肩膀掉头走开了。 一会儿， 他突然从后追了上来， 把笔塞到我手里。  "}

22
00:02:16.020 --> 00:02:22.923
{"en":"Though he kept throwing up his arms in despair,  he readily accepted the $5 I give him. ^ ","ch":"虽然他绝望地举起双手， 但他毫不迟疑地收下了我付给他的5镑钱。  "}

23
00:02:23.073 --> 00:02:29.950
{"en":"I felt especially pleased with my wonderful bargain -- until I got back to the ship. ^ ","ch":"在回到船上之前， 我一直为我的绝妙的讨价还价而洋洋得意。  "}

24
00:02:30.100 --> 00:02:42.175
{"en":"No matter how hard I tried,  it was impossible to fill this beautiful pen with ink and to this day it has never written a single world! ^ ","ch":"然而不管我如何摆弄， 那枝漂亮的钢笔就是吸不进墨水来。 直到今天， 那枝笔连一个字也没写过！  "}

